From f72b4bcda9b4d1c4b25e840388cbbf18a9487d30 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: chiranjeevipattigidi <chiranjeevi.pattigidi@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 10:41:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [Tensile/TensileLite] Compile one arch at a time for sccache
 compatibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Tensile and TensileLite previously compiled GPU kernels by invoking clang
with all --offload-arch flags in one command, producing a fat bundled object.
sccache refuses these calls with "Non-cacheable: multiple input files" because
it cannot compute a per-arch cache key for a multi-target output, causing
~5,000 cache misses per math-libs build.

This change compiles one architecture at a time (each call is a single
source → single object, which sccache can cache independently), then
re-bundles the per-arch objects into the fat object using
clang-offload-bundler. The pipeline output is identical — the same fat
object with the same per-arch .hsaco contents — but each per-arch compile
is now independently cached by sccache.

Changes:
- shared/tensile/Tensile/BuildCommands/SourceCommands.py:
  - Add _compileSingleArchObjectFile() for per-arch compilation
  - Add _bundleObjectFiles() to re-bundle per-arch objects into fat object
  - Update _compileSourceObjectFile() to use per-arch path when bundler
    is available; falls back to original single-call path if not

- projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Component.py:
  - Compiler.__call__: compile per-arch when target_list > 1; stores
    per-arch paths on instance for Source.py to bundle
  - Bundler.bundle(): new method to bundle per-arch objects into fat object

- projects/hipblaslt/tensilelite/Tensile/Toolchain/Source.py:
  - After compiler(), detect pending per-arch objects and call bundler.bundle()
    before proceeding to the unbundle step
